ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Unique number for each sample, consecutively numbered from 1-4224
Plate number of qPCR
Well in which sample was plated
Consolidated ID (participant ID and sample ID)
Collection status of sample (MS is missing)
ID of unique sample, including sample type, timepoint, and aliquot number.
Type of sample (plasma, serum, saliva)
For awakening saliva, day of collection
Timepoint of collection for both awakening and stress samples
Category of sample (awakening, misc, stress, fasting)
Notes about the sample, in particular visual appearance.
Natural log transformed nd1 copies/ul of sample (mtDNA)
b2m copies/ul of sample (mtDNA)
Natural log transformed b2m copies/ul of sample (nDNA)
b2m copies/ul of sample (nDNA)
Standard deviation between two measures of nd1
Standard deviation between two measures of b2m
Coefficient of variation between two measures of nd1
Coefficient of variation between two measures of b2m
